      "onchain_auto/0xbc452fdc8f851d7c5b72e1fe74dfb63bb793d511/contracts/Periphery/ClaimCampaigns.sol:233"
    ],
    "claim": "A locked campaign can point to any external `claimLockup.tokenLocker`. During `claimTokens`, the contract marks the user as claimed and decrements campaign inventory before calling `createPlan`, but it never verifies that the locker actually pulled tokens or minted a lockup/vesting position for the claimant.",
    "impact": "A malicious or buggy locker can make claims appear successful while delivering no locked position at all. The victim permanently loses their Merkle entitlement, and the approved locker can later take the underlying tokens.",
    "paths": [
      "Attacker creates a locked campaign whose `tokenLocker` implements `createPlan()` as a no-op that simply returns.",
      "A victim submits a valid Merkle claim; `claimed[campaignId][victim]` is set to true and `campaign.amount` is reduced.",
      "Because no postcondition is checked, the transaction succeeds even though no plan was created and the approved locker still controls the tokens."
    ]
  },
